    <h1>Normalization</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Wikipedia &middot; <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Database_normalization"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>Database normalization</a> &middot; CC BY-SA 4.0</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Normalization</strong> eliminates redundancy by decomposing tables based on functional dependencies. Each normal form (1NF through BCNF) removes a specific kind of anomaly. The goal: every fact is stored exactly once, so updates cannot create inconsistencies.</p>
    </div>

